Euro Declines Versus Dollar, Yen After S&P Lowers Italy’s Credit Ratings

-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 
2011-09-19T22:27:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/euro-declines-versus-dollar-yen-after-s-p-lowers-italy-s-credit-ratings.html
The euro fell after  Italy  had its
long- and short-term sovereign credit ratings cut to A/A-1 from
A+/A-1+ by Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services.  The 17-nation currency declined to $1.3626 at 8:24 a.m. in
Sydney from $1.3686 in  New York  yesterday. It dropped to 104.36
yen from 104.82.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candice Zachariahs in Sydney at 
 czachariahs2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benjamin Purvis at 
 bpurvis@bloomberg.net  